<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911108-0019</DOCNO><DOCID>911108-0019.</DOCID><HL>   Canada House of Commons   Clears Tighter Gun Control</HL><DATE>11/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><RE>CANADA (CN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)</RE><LP>   OTTAWA -- The Canadian House of Commons approved by a voteof 189-14 legislation to toughen gun controls.   The bill was sent to the Senate, which is expected toapprove it, making it law.</LP><TEXT>   The legislation would allow the government to carrythrough its plan to limit the magazine size of semiautomaticrifles and shotguns to five cartridges. Many Canadiansdemanded such a restriction after 14 women were killed twoyears ago at a Montreal school, the Ecole Polytechnique, by aman named Marc Lepine who was armed with a 30-shotsemi-automatic rifle.   The legislation also provides for a 28-day waiting periodbefore a firearms acquisition certificate is issued to aprospective gun-owner. The waiting period is to allow for athorough investigation of applicants.   The Canadian Association of Chiefs of Police and themayors of many towns and cities said in a joint statementthat the legislation was &quot;a step in the right direction,&quot; butthey said they would have preferred tougher restrictions. AGallup poll said 79% of Canadians favor tougher gun controls.</TEXT></DOC>